#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:41
msgid ""
"All tables included in a Darwin Core Archive *must* include a unique "
"identifier column"
msgstr ""

#.  Please also consult the documentation for xref:metadata-recommendations-and-requirements.adoc[requirements for the EML file].
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:43
msgid ""
"Data published with the support of one of the programmes or projects managed "
"by GBIF (e.g. https://www.gbif.org/programme/82243[BID], https://www.gbif."
"org/programme/82629[BIFA], https://www.gbif.org/programme/82219[CESP], "
"https://www.gbif.org/news/59knqJp4BWbh6gnFh7E8qR/gbif-advances-edna-data-"
"integration-to-support-global-research-and-decision-making[SPLICE]) have "
"stricter data quality requirements than data published outside of these "
"programmes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:46
msgid ""
"It is the publisher's responsibility to obscure sensitive species "
"information. Please consult the https://docs.gbif.org/sensitive-species-best-"
"practices/master/en/[Current Best Practices for Generalizing Sensitive "
"Species Occurrence Data]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "Data quality requirements for checklists"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:50
msgid ""
"https://www.gbif.org/dataset/search?type=CHECKLIST[Checklist datasets] "
"provide a catalogue, rapid summary or baseline inventory of a set of named "
"organisms, or taxa. While they may include additional details like local "
"species names or specimen citations, checklists typically categorize "
"information along taxonomic, geographic, and thematic lines or some "
"combination of the three."
msgstr ""

