#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "{taxon} taxonID [[taxonID]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:363
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_taxonID[_dwc:taxonID_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:366
msgid ""
"A unique identifier for the taxon, allowing the same taxon to be recognized "
"across dataset versions as well as through data downloads and use. Ideally, "
"the taxonID is a persistent global unique identifier. As a minimum "
"requirement, it has to be unique within the published dataset. It allows to "
"recognize the same set of taxon information over time when the dataset "
"indexing is refreshed; it links additional data like images or occurrence "
"records; and it makes it possible to cite records e.g. in usage reports or "
"in publications. This means that the taxonID needs to reliably stay with the "
"taxon information at source and to consistently refer to the same set of "
"taxon information in published datasets and any underlying source data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:369
#, no-wrap
msgid "{taxon} scientificName [[scientificName]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:370
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_scientificName[_dwc:scientificName_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:373
msgid ""
"The full scientific name, including authorship and year of the name where "
"applicable. In the context of a checklist, the scientific name is the core "
"data element of a taxon list or hierarchy that the dataset is set out to "
"collate and publish."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:375
msgid ""
"Depending on the purpose of the checklist, scientific names may be of any "
"hierarchical level, though typically would be of species rank or below for, "
"e.g., regional floristic or faunistic checklists, Red List collations, or "
"thematic inventories like marine organisms or taxonomic revisions of species "
"groups. If the checklist is intended to publish a hierarchy (tree-like "
"structure), add separate entries for the relevant upper taxonomic ranks, e."
"g. kingdom, class and family, and link them into a hierarchical structure "
"using the parentNameUsageID (see below) to support unambiguous "
"interpretation of the checklist entries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:377
msgid ""
"Valid scientific names are Latin names following the syntax rules of the "
"respective taxon group (e.g. botanical nomenclature). Not permitted are, i."
"e., working names (`Mallomonas sp.4`), common names (`fruit fly`), or names "
"containing identification qualifiers (`Anemone cf. nemorosa`). If common "
"names are used, they should be supplied in addition to the scientific names, "
"using the <<vernacularName>> set of fields."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:380
#, no-wrap
msgid "{taxon} taxonRank [[taxonRank]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:381
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_taxonRank[_dwc:taxonRank_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:384
msgid ""
"The taxonomic rank of the supplied scientific name. The taxon rank supports "
"the interpretation of the scientific name during indexing and supports "
"matching the checklist records to the core taxonomy, especially in the case "
"of names at the genus level or above (monomials). While the format of higher "
"taxon names in some groups contains indicators of their rank, this is not "
"consistent across or even within groups, and cannot be reliably used for "
"interpretation. For placing names correctly, explicitly specifying the taxon "
"rank, alongside information on the higher taxonomy, is an important "
"criterion. For practical purposes, the ranks used have to be (major) Linnean "
"ranks: kingdom, phylum, class, order, family, genus, and species. Both Latin "
"and English terms are accepted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:387
#, no-wrap
msgid "{taxon} kingdom [[kingdom]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:388
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_kingdom[_dwc:kingdom_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:391
msgid ""
"The full scientific name specifying the kingdom that the scientific name is "
"classified under and other higher taxonomy, if possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:393
msgid ""
"With scientific names, there are numerous cases where the matching of a "
"given name against the core taxonomy is unsure or ambiguous. This is the "
"case, for example, with homonyms (identical names exist for different "
"organisms, usually across groups), newly described names that are not yet "
"part of the existing taxonomic tree, or spelling variants (typos, "
"hyphenation etc). To support exact matching of a scientific name against the "
"core taxonomy, additional names at higher ranks help interpretation and "
"error prevention. For datasets where the hierarchical representation in the "
"published data is not important, higher-level names can be supplied as part "
"of the record itself by adding the relevant DarwinCore fields, similar to "
"occurrence datasets."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:395
msgid ""
"Names should be scientific (Latin) names at major Linnean ranks, like "
"`Animalia` (`kingdom`) or `Rosaceae` (`family`). Not: common names "
"(`animals`), abbreviations (`Rosac.`), intermediate rank levels (`Tetrapoda` "
"(`superclass`)), or polyphyletic or non-taxonomic groupings (`algae`, "
"`herbivore`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:398
#, no-wrap
msgid "{taxon} parentNameUsageID [[parentNameUsageID]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:399
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_parentNameUsageID[_dwc:parentNameUsageID_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:402
msgid ""
"The taxonID of the next available higher-ranked (parent) entry within the "
"checklist dataset, if higher taxon names are supplied as separate entries in "
"the list. This supports the representation of the dataset as a hierarchy, e."
"g. for the publication of a taxonomy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:405
#, no-wrap
msgid "{taxon} acceptedNameUsageID [[acceptedNameUsageID]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:406
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_acceptedNameUsageID[_dwc:acceptedNameUsageID_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:409
msgid ""
"Within the record of a synonym, the taxonID of the accepted taxon name entry "
"within the checklist dataset, if both synonyms and accepted names are "
"supplied. This supports the representation of synonymy for a taxonomic "
"dataset."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:412
#, no-wrap
msgid "{taxon} vernacularName [[vernacularName]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:413
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_vernacularName[_dwc:vernacularName_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:416
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:423
msgid ""
"When supplied, also add at least the language of the name, using ISO 639-1 "
"language codes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:419
#, no-wrap
msgid "{taxon} higherClassification [[higherClassification]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:420
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/terms/#dwc:higherClassification[_dwc:higherClassification_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:426
#, no-wrap
msgid "{location} countryCode [[countryCode]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:427
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_countryCode[_dwc:countryCode_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:430
msgid ""
"A two-letter standard abbreviation for the country, territory or island of "
"the occurrence <<locality>>. Information on the collection or observation "
"<<locality>> (geographic reference) is essential for any record. The country "
"code is the proposed minimum standard to supply this information. The format "
"for this field follows the https://www.iso.org/iso-3166-country-codes."
"html[ISO 3166-1-alpha-2 standard] for country codes. Those are two-letter "
"codes for each country, territory or island; lists can be found online. "
"Publishers who wish to supply the country name, in addition, may add the "
"appropriate element. In most cases, occurrences can be linked to a specific "
"country, territory or island. In cases where it is not possible to supply a "
"country code (e.g. marine data outside of coastal zones), geographical "
"coordinates should be supplied instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:433
#, no-wrap
msgid "{location} decimalLatitude [[decimalLatitude]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:434
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_decimalLatitude[_dwc:decimalLatitude_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:437
msgid ""
"The geographic latitude in decimal degrees. Where coordinate values are "
"available <<decimalLongitude>> should be filled also. Valid values lie "
"between `-90` and `90` incl. (latitude = 0 is the equator). Decimal "
"coordinate values provide a geolocation of the occurrence that is much more "
"informative than the country name alone, and that is stable over time "
"(unlike the borders of countries). Many data use cases require coordinates "
"if the data are to be of value or usable at all, for example, species "
"distribution modelling or population studies in specific areas."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:439
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:448
msgid ""
"Several issues concerning coordinates are encountered frequently. While the "
"indexing process makes efforts to identify such cases and propose "
"corrections, e.g. by plausibility-testing coordinates against country names, "
"attention is needed already at the level of data preparation and "
"publication. Such issues include transformation errors (resulting from e.g. "
"conversion of degrees-minutes-seconds into decimal values), accidental "
"swapping of values, either in the dataset or during the mapping process "
"(latitude and longitude are reversed), or negation of values (transposition "
"of locations from north to south, east to west or vice versa through the "
"accidental or systematic loss or addition of minus-values). Additional "
"points to keep in mind during data preparation are technical defaults (e.g. "
"database settings substituting 0-values instead of unknown values resulting "
"in records supplying lat/long as `0/0`); over-precision of data by automatic "
"number-padding (`lat -17.79200000` where `lat -17.792` would be "
"appropriate), or the need to blur coordinate precision e.g. the protection "
"of sensitive species. Also note that gridded data, i.e. where coordinates "
"represent centroids of grid cells in a field survey rather than the actual "
"occurrence <<locality>>, may be better represented by publishing the dataset "
"as event data rather than as occurrence records. Especially in such cases, "
"it is essential also to supply the <<coordinateUncertaintyInMeters>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:442
#, no-wrap
msgid "{location} decimalLongitude [[decimalLongitude]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:443
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_decimalLongitude[_dwc:decimalLongitude_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:446
msgid ""
"The geographic longitude in decimal degrees. Where coordinate values are "
"available <<decimalLatitude>> should be filled also. Valid values lie "
"between -180 and 180 incl. (longitude = 0 is the Greenwich Meridian). "
"Decimal coordinate values provide a geolocation of the occurrence that is "
"much more informative than the country name alone, and that is stable over "
"time (unlike the borders of countries). Many data use cases require "
"coordinates if the data are to be of value or usable at all, for example, "
"species distribution modelling or population studies in specific areas."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:451
#, no-wrap
msgid "{location} geodeticDatum [[geodeticDatum]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:452
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_geodeticDatum[_dwc:geodeticDatum_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:455
msgid ""
"The coordinate system and set of reference points upon which the geographic "
"coordinates are based. Different geodetic systems exist, and the exact "
"<<locality>> of a point depends on which reference system the coordinates "
"refer to. This is why the system should always be explicitly named when "
"known: depending on the geographic region, the datum shift between two "
"systems can vary from zero to hundreds of meters for a given point. When no "
"value is supplied, GBIF's indexing process assumes the reference system to "
"be WGS 84 (World Geodetic System 1984, a global approximation at sea level "
"and, i.e., base of GPS data); but the more frequently the geodetic datum can "
"be supplied explicitly by data publishers, the more reliable the geographic "
"representation of occurrences will become, e.g. through datum conversion. It "
"is likewise important to explicitly document the lack of knowledge of the "
"system used, as this increases confidence in data interpretation. Examples: "
"`WGS84`; `EPSG:4326`; `unknown`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:458
#, no-wrap
msgid "{location} coordinateUncertaintyInMeters [[coordinateUncertaintyInMeters]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:459
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_coordinateUncertaintyInMeters[_dwc:coordinateUncertaintyInMeters_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:462
msgid ""
"The horizontal distance from the given <<decimalLatitude>> and "
"<<decimalLongitude>> in meters, describing the smallest circle containing "
"the whole of the Location. This is an indicator of the accuracy of the "
"coordinate location, described as the radius of a circle around the stated "
"point location. It allows estimating the potential distance of the real "
"occurrence location from the recorded values and largely depends on the "
"methodology used in coordinate determination. Thus, the value may be "
"specific to or estimated from the methodology or device used for "
"geolocating, e.g. `30` (reasonable lower limit of a GPS reading under good "
"conditions if the actual precision was not recorded at the time). Note that "
"`0` (zero) is not a valid value for this measure. If the value is unknown or "
"not applicable, the value should be empty (null). If for some reason the "
"`coordinateUncertaintyInMeters` was artificially increased, for example by "
"rounding the coordinate values, the fields <<informationWithheld>> or "
"<<dataGeneralizations>> must be filled in addition. Examples: `30`; `71`; "
"`[empty]`. Not: `0`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:465
#, no-wrap
msgid "{location} country [[country]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:466
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_country[_dwc:country_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:470
#, no-wrap
msgid "{location} locationID [[locationID]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:471
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_locationID[_dwc:locationID_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:474
msgid ""
"An internal or external reference that links to a set of data describing the "
"sample event location, if available. Example: `http://www.geonames."
"org/10793757/dnb-6.html`. Note: if such a reference cannot be meaningfully "
"supplied, consider supplying more location detail, e.g. through use of the "
"data elements `locality`, `minimumElevationInMeters`, "
"`minimumDepthInMeters`, `stateProvince`, `locationRemarks`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:477
#, no-wrap
msgid "{location} footprintWKT [[footprintWKT]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:478
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_footprintWKT[_dwc:footprintWKT_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:481
msgid ""
"An alternative area description, specifying the location of the sample event "
"in Well-known text (WKT) markup language. A WKT representation of the shape "
"(footprint, geometry) that defines the location. This differs from the point-"
"radius representation that is combined from the elements "
"<<decimalLatitude>>, <<decimalLongitude>> and "
"<<coordinateUncertaintyInMeters>> in that it can define shapes that are not "
"circles. Example: a one-degree bounding box with opposite corners at "
"(`longitude`=`10`, `latitude`=`20`) and (`longitude`=`11`, `latitude`=`21`) "
"would be expressed in well-known text as `POLYGON ((10 20, 11 20, 11 21, 10 "
"21, 10 20))`. Note that it is possible to supply both a point-radius and a "
"footprintWKT location for the same sample event."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:484
#, no-wrap
msgid "{location} locality [[locality]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:485
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_locality[_dwc:locality_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:488
msgid ""
"Less specific geographic information can be provided in other geographic "
"terms (dwc:higherGeography, dwc:continent, dwc:country, dwc:stateProvince, "
"dwc:county, dwc:municipality, dwc:waterBody, dwc:island, dwc:islandGroup). "
"This term may contain information modified from the original to correct "
"perceived errors or standardize the description."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:490
#, no-wrap
msgid "{occurrence} occurrenceID [[occurrenceID]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:491
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_occurrenceID[_dwc:occurrenceID_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:494
msgid ""
"A unique identifier for the occurrence, allowing the same occurrence to be "
"recognized across dataset versions as well as through data downloads. As a "
"minimum requirement, it has to be unique within the published dataset, but "
"can also be a globally unique identifier. It allows users to recognize the "
"same occurrence over time when the dataset indexing is refreshed. "
"OccurrenceIDs also link additional data like images to the record, and it "
"makes it possible to cite records. This means that the occurrenceID needs to "
"reliably stay with the occurrence at source, and to consistently refer to "
"the same occurrence in published datasets and any underlying source data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:496
msgid ""
"The occurrenceID in a dataset helps GBIF identify whether an occurrence "
"record is new. If it is new, GBIF assigns it a new unique gbifID. Some "
"publishers include information, such as the collection or institution code, "
"within the occurrenceID. However, if the collection or institution changes, "
"the occurrenceID must also change, even though the actual occurrence record "
"remains the same. This practice can lead to unnecessary instability in "
"occurrenceIDs and gbifIDs. If possible, we now encourage publishers to use "
"an occurrenceIDs with more stability, that do not encode information about "
"the occurrence or specimen. For example, a simple large integer or UUID."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:498
msgid ""
"An important part of GBIF data processing is to assign a stable gbifID each "
"new record. This is a somewhat complex process that uses the occurrenceID, "
"catalogNumber, collectionCode, and institutionCode in combination with the "
"GBIF datasetKey to either mint a new identifier or reuse an existing one. "
"When publishers do not supply an occurrenceID, GBIF processing will "
"construct an identifier using the so-called triplet code (catalogNumber, "
"collectionCode and institutionCode)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:500
msgid ""
"If a previously published dataset alters more than 50% of its exsisting "
"occurrenceIDs, it will get flagged by our link:https://github.com/gbif/"
"ingestion-management/issues[ingestion management system]. Typically, a "
"publisher will get an e-mail from GBIF within a day or two asking for a file "
"mapping the old occurrenceIDs to the new occurrenceIDs. A GBIF data blog "
"post has been written on the topic of id stability link:https://data-blog."
"gbif.org/post/improve-identifier-stability/[here]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:503
#, no-wrap
msgid "{occurrence} individualCount [[individualCount]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:504
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_individualCount[_dwc:individualCount_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:507
msgid ""
"Use the `individualCount` field to capture the number of individuals for the "
"species associated with the occurrence."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:510
#, no-wrap
msgid "{occurrence} organismQuantity [[organismQuantity]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:511
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_organismQuantity[_dwc:organismQuantity_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:514
msgid ""
"To record the quantity of a species occurrence. Use together with "
"<<organismQuantityType>> to specify the quantity e.g., `organismQuantity`: "
"`5`/ `organismQuantityType`: `individuals`. `organismQuantity`: `r` / "
"`organismQuantityType`: `BraunBlanquetScale`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:517
#, no-wrap
msgid "{occurrence} organismQuantityType [[organismQuantityType]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:518
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_organismQuantityType[_dwc:organismQuantityType_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:521
msgid ""
"To record the quantity type of a species occurrence. Use together with "
"<<organismQuantity>> to specify the type of measurement e.g., "
"`organismQuantity`: `5`/ `organismQuantityType`: `individuals`. "
"`organismQuantity`: `r` / `organismQuantityType`: `BraunBlanquetScale`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:524
#, no-wrap
msgid "{occurrence} occurrenceStatus [[occurrenceStatus]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:525
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_occurrenceStatus[_dwc:occurrenceStatus_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:528
msgid ""
"Note: this applies to associated occurrence data, not to the sample event "
"itself. A qualifier for individual occurrence records, marking a taxon as "
"either present or absent at a location during the sampling event. Since "
"sample datasets document the sampling effort exerted during the event, it "
"can often be valuable to not only document taxa as being present (observed, "
"collected) at the location at the time, but also to record negative "
"occurrences (absences) for taxa that could be reasonably expected, but were "
"not encountered in the event. An example is a floristic survey that "
"estimates the abundance or coverage of plants in a certain area, working "
"from a list of species that were encountered on earlier surveys of that same "
"region. Recommendation: use the standard values of either `present` or "
"`absent` to mark individual occurrence records."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:531
#, no-wrap
msgid "{occurrence} catalogNumber [[catalogNumber]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:532
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_catalogNumber[_dwc:catalogNumber_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:535
msgid ""
"An identifier (preferably unique) for the record within the dataset or "
"collection."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:540
#, no-wrap
msgid "{material} associatedSequences [[associatedSequences]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:541
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_associatedSequences[_dwc:associatedSequences_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:544
msgid ""
"A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, accession "
"number, global unique identifier, URI) of genetic sequence information "
"associated with the dwc:MaterialEntity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:547
#, no-wrap
msgid "{identification} typeStatus [[typeStatus]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:548
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_typeStatus[_dwc:typeStatus_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:551
msgid ""
"The nomenclatural type status of a specimen or name. Please choose a value "
"from the GBIF controlled vocabulary for https://registry.gbif.org/vocabulary/"
"TypeStatus[type status]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:554
#, no-wrap
msgid "{identification} identifiedBy [[identifiedBy]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:555
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_identifiedBy[_dwc:identifiedBy_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:558
msgid ""
"A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or "
"organizations who assigned the dwc:Taxon to the subject."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:563
#, no-wrap
msgid "{event} eventDate [[eventDate]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:564
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_eventDate[_dwc:eventDate_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:567
msgid ""
"Dates and times published in Darwin Core should use the https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/ISO_8601[ISO 8601-1:2019] standard. Please see the following "
"https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-processing/temporal-"
"interpretation[documentation] for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:570
#, no-wrap
msgid "{event} eventTime [[eventTime]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:571
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_eventTime[_dwc:eventTime_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:575
#, no-wrap
msgid "{event} eventID [[eventID]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:576
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_eventID[_dwc:eventID_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:579
msgid ""
"A unique identifier for the sampling event, allowing to link individual "
"occurrences to a specific event, and to cross-reference events to document e."
"g. time series (resampling) or synchronized sampling across a wider area."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:581
msgid ""
"The eventID can be a persistent global unique identifier, or an identifier "
"specific to the dataset. Its main function is to allow linking to related "
"data (occurrences, other sampling events, site images etc.). While dataset-"
"specific eventIDs are sufficient to refer to occurence records published "
"within the same dataset, it is worth considering that very simple IDs like "
"numbers could easily reoccur in other, unrelated datasets, and make external "
"linkages ambiguous. In addition, the eventID needs to reliably stay with the "
"sampling event information at source and consistently refer to the same "
"event, or else any data links will be broken."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:584
#, no-wrap
msgid "{event} samplingProtocol [[samplingProtocol]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:585
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_samplingProtocol[_dwc:samplingProtocol_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:588
msgid ""
"The name of, reference to, or description of the method or protocol used "
"during a sample event. Sample events typically use specific methods or "
"follow certain protocols that standardize the sampling effort to a certain "
"degree. Knowledge about the sampling protocol gives users additional "
"information that is helpful for the interpretation of the attached "
"occurrence records, e.g. what kind of organisms to expect or not expect "
"within the dataset and whether the absence of a recording signifies absence "
"in nature, or was outside the target group of the applied sampling "
"methodology (e.g. `UV light trap`). If a more detailed description of the "
"method or protocol exists, providing a reference is strongly encouraged (e."
"g. http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1466-8238.2009.00467.x[Penguins from space: "
"faecal stains reveal the location of emperor penguin colonies]. While there "
"is no controlled vocabulary for this element, the goal is to, across "
"datasets, gradually assemble a library of references for reuse, and to allow "
"users to identify datasets that are based on comparable methods and "
"protocols."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:591
#, no-wrap
msgid "{event} sampleSizeValue [[sampleSizeValue]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:592
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_sampleSizeValue[_dwc:sampleSizeValue_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:595
msgid ""
"Note: <<sampleSizeUnit>> should always be shared with the corresponding "
"sampleSizeValue."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:597
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:606
msgid ""
"A numeric value and the corresponding unit for the value, specifying the "
"size of an individual sample in the sampling event. The two sampleSize "
"fields always go together, and specify the size of an individual sample "
"within a sample event. The sample size can relate to time duration, a "
"spatial length (e.g. of a trawl), an area or a volume. A vegetation plot, "
"for example, may have a `sampleSizeValue` of `2` with a `sampleSizeUnit` of "
"`square kilometer`. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled "
"vocabulary for the <<sampleSizeUnit>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:600
#, no-wrap
msgid "{event} sampleSizeUnit [[sampleSizeUnit]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:601
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_sampleSizeUnit[_dwc:sampleSizeUnit_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:604
msgid ""
"Note: <<sampleSizeValue>> should always be shared with the corresponding "
"sampleSizeUnit."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:609
#, no-wrap
msgid "{event} parentEventID [[parentEventID]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:610
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_parentEventID[_dwc:parentEventID_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:613
msgid ""
"A cross-reference to the eventID of a broader event, e.g. a long-term "
"monitoring project that the specific event is a part of or a general "
"vegetation survey of a larger area that is comprised of a number of sub-"
"plots. To be able to reference a parent event, this event needs to be "
"specified as a separate entry, typically within the same dataset, carrying "
"its own eventID. Refer to the eventID of the parent event in the sample "
"event record to specify the relationship between the two entries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:616
#, no-wrap
msgid "{event} samplingEffort [[samplingEffort]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:617
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://dwc.tdwg.org/list/#dwc_samplingEffort[_dwc:samplingEffort_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:620
msgid ""
"The measure for the amount of effort that was expended during a sampling "
"event. The amount of effort expended during a sampling event often "
"influences the result. It included factors like the number of observers "
"involved, or the total time spent collecting, the number of traps exposed "
"over a certain amount of time, the total distance covered, and the mode of "
"transport used, while surveying a plot, etc. Examples of sampling effort are "
"`40 trap-nights`, `10 observer-hours`. While there is no controlled "
"vocabulary, the recommendation is to keep this information brief and "
"factual, giving users enough information to compare between sampling events."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:624
#, no-wrap
msgid "DNA_sequence [[DNA_sequence]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:625
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://rs.gbif.org/extension/gbif/1.0/dna_derived_data_2024-07-11.xml#DNA_sequence[_DNA_sequence_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:628
msgid ""
"A nucleotide sequence composed exclusively of uppercase IUPAC nucleotide "
"characters (G, A, T, C, R, Y, M, K, S, W, H, B, V, D, N), provided in 5′–3′ "
"orientation, with no gap characters, whitespace, quality scores, sequence "
"descriptions, or identifiers. Intended for use in taxon identification and "
"biodiversity assessment. The target gene or barcode locus from which the "
"sequence is derived should be specified using the <<target_gene>> term."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:631
#, no-wrap
msgid "target_gene [[target_gene]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:632
#, no-wrap
msgid "\thttps://w3id.org/mixs/0000044[_mixs:target_gene_]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:635
msgid ""
"Targeted gene or locus name for marker gene studies. Please use a value from "
"https://registry.gbif.org/vocabulary/target_gene[GBIF's controlled "
"vocabulary for target_gene]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:639
#, no-wrap
msgid "Status [[Status]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:641
#, no-wrap
msgid "Required information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:644
msgid ""
"The terms constitute the minimum formal requirements for publishing an "
"occurrence dataset. GBIF will not accept a dataset without these terms and "
"will not index the records. While these items are mandatory for publishing "
"the dataset, they are only the starting point. The usefulness of the "
"published data will still be severely limited unless additional information "
"is supplied."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:645
#, no-wrap
msgid "Strongly recommended information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:648
msgid ""
"In addition to the mandatory terms, GBIF strongly recommends completing "
"several more fields that help improve the usefulness of the dataset:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:650
msgid ""
"some information supports the integration into global data resources and "
"prevents ambiguity, e.g. in matching scientific names that could apply to "
"more than one organism (homonyms) to the correct place within the backbone "
"taxonomy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:651
msgid ""
"more precise geo-location data (coordinates) significantly increase the "
"usefulness of the data for a wide range of use cases"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:652
msgid ""
"additional qualifiers for some data elements, e.g. coordinates, support the "
"interpretation of those elements and help users to better estimate their "
"usefulness for a given data use case"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:653
msgid ""
"some data redundancy supports quality control and error detection (e.g. "
"testing country codes against coordinates where both are supplied)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:654
msgid ""
"last but not least, the richer the spectrum of available information of a "
"dataset is, the more potential usage areas it becomes available for, meaning "
"the dataset will be more widely accessible and used, and cited more often"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:655
#, no-wrap
msgid "Share if available"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/data-quality-recommendations.adoc:657
msgid ""
"If additional data are available, consider sharing them to increase the "
"usefulness of your published data."
msgstr ""
